  "prompt": "Is there an inpatient Drug and Alcohol Rehab Center in Shasta County California?",
  "response": "Yes, there are inpatient drug and alcohol rehab centers in Shasta County, California. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Visions of the Cross**\n   - **Address:** 3640-3652 El Portal Dr, Redding, CA 96002\n   - **Phone:** (530) 223-0208\n   - **Services:** Inpatient and outpatient treatment for substance abuse, detoxification, and residential treatment.\n\n2. **Empire Recovery Center**\n   - **Address:** 1237 California St, Redding, CA 96001\n   - **Phone:** (530) 242-1688\n   - **Services:** Residential treatment, detox, and outpatient services for substance abuse.\n\n3. **Northern Valley Indian Health, Inc.**\n   - **Address:** 2555 Airpark Dr, Redding, CA 96001\n   - **Phone:** (530) 224-2700\n   - **Services:** Inpatient and outpatient substance abuse treatment, culturally sensitive programs.\n\nIt's important to contact these facilities directly to inquire about availability, specific programs, and to see if they meet your individual needs. Additionally, you might want to check with your insurance provider to see if any of these facilities are covered under your plan.",
